wiki.summary: Challenging another concept, “해야 (HEYA)” is a song that begins with an intense rap, an overwhelming atmosphere in the chorus, and conveys an ever-changing charm. It is an impressive song with an addictive melody that can be sung by all gender of all ages, and the lyrics are reconstructed into an eyebrow version in 2024 with the classic story “The Tiger Who Loved the Sun.” “해야 (HEYA)” is a track of IVE’s exploration of the hip-hop genre that focuses on the girls' powerful vocals and flowy rap. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Challenging another concept, “해야 (HEYA)” is a song that begins with an intense rap, an overwhelming atmosphere in the chorus, and conveys an ever-changing charm. It is an impressive song with an addictive melody that can be sung by all gender of all ages, and the lyrics are reconstructed into an eyebrow version in 2024 with the classic story “The Tiger Who Loved the Sun.” “해야 (HEYA)” is a track of IVE’s exploration of the hip-hop genre that focuses on the girls' powerful vocals and flowy rap. The lyrics includes an oriental folktale style that talks about achieving victory as you are being enchanted by their voices. Read more on Last.fm.
